SYNOPSIS

    To get logger object:

     use Log::ger::Like::LogAny '$log';

    or:

     use Log::ger::Like::LogAny;

    To log:

     $log->debug("blah ...");
    
     if ($log->is_trace) {
         $log->tracef("Foo is %s", $foo);
     }

    To set output, use one of the available Log::ger::Output::*. You can
    send logs to Log::Any using Log::ger::Output::LogAny.

DESCRIPTION

    This module mimics Log::Any-like logging interface.

SEE ALSO

    Log::ger

    Log::Any

